{
  "texts": [
    "Next, define the selection mechanisms.",
    "Common interaction methods include a brush on the time axis for the line chart, dual brushes for the scatter plot, and click interactions for the bar chart.",
    "Then, the transform filter should be applied to the other charts.",
    "• Layout organization: When generating new visualizations, we set the charts to the same size and arrange them sequentially.",
    "If the user selects charts to merge multiple views, we allow selecting up to six charts to avoid excessive cognitive load."
  ]
}